<p id="Par47">The singularity at 
 <italic>q</italic>
 <sub>therm</sub>(
 <italic>Δt</italic> 
 <italic>=</italic> 0) arises because of the assumption of instantaneous intrusion. This assumption is reasonable because the intrusion period is on the order of days whereas the gas generation occurs over decades to thousands of years. To avoid the singularity when plotting at time 
 <italic>t</italic> « 1 yr and when quoting initial fluxes, we average 
 <italic>q</italic>
 <sub>therm</sub> over a preceding time period 
